{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RraHkhhQ2ZTtY9D7ixEUQw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The ConfigMap `config-audit` is created with a full, non-empty `findings.txt`. No cluster settings were touched.\n\nHere's a summary of what the audit found:\n\n**5 CRITICAL findings:**\n- `SEC-001` — `xpack.security.enabled: false` on all nodes — zero authentication, complete open access\n- `SEC-004/005` — HTTP TLS and transport TLS both disabled — all traffic plaintext\n- `SEC-007` — `network.host: 0.0.0.0` + **no Kubernetes NetworkPolicy** — any pod in any namespace can hit port 9200/9300 with full admin access\n- `SEC-009` — Security audit logging disabled — no forensic trail\n\n**5 HIGH findings:**\n- No credential Secrets provisioned anywhere in the namespace\n- Basic license — RBAC, field-level security, and document-level security are unavailable\n- Container and pod `securityContext` both empty — no `runAsNonRoot`, no capability dropping, `allowPrivilegeEscalation` not restricted\n- `cluster.initial_master_nodes` still in live config (deprecated, breaks ES 9.x)\n- All 3 nodes carry combined master+data+ingest roles — no dedicated master separation\n\n**5 MEDIUM findings** covering JVM heap (512m, below recommended 1g), no snapshot repository, ILM policy references warm/cold tiers that don't exist, `OnDelete` update strategy with no runbook, and the `require.tier=hot` shard routing constraint on `audit-index`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":553,"cache_read_input_tokens":56413,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":553},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2e39a45e-ba5e-4e98-9e88-4501f9cbe38a","uuid":"d2e26f5b-04ac-49c8-ab50-43f7f95a664a","request_id"